title: The journal of Sir Walter Scott,
author: Scott, Walter
snippet: Lord M. and Lady Abercromby called this morning,  and a world of people besides, among others honest Mr. Wilson, late of Wilsontown, who took so much care of me at London, sending  fresh eggs and all sorts of good things.
